Preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees. Core, seed, and remove white veins from the @Poblano Pepper{1%unit}, then thinly slice. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @Yellow Onion{1%unit}. Thinly slice the @Portobello Mushrooms{2%unit}. Halve the @Lime{1%unit}. Finely chop the @Tomato{1%unit} and @Cilantro{1%bunch}, keeping the stems and leaves separate. Mince the @Garlic{2%clove}.

Heat @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the onions, sliced pepper, and half the @Cumin{1%teaspoon} to the pan, then season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, tossing, for ~{5-7%minutes}, or until slightly caramelized. Set aside.

Halve, pit, and scoop out the flesh of the @Avocado{1%unit}. Using a fork, mash the avocado in a #bowl{} with a squeeze of lime. Stir in the chopped tomato and 3/4 the cilantro leaves. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.

In the same pan you cooked the peppers in, heat another @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} over medium heat. Add the mushrooms and season with salt and pepper. Cook, tossing, for about ~{5%minutes}, or until golden brown. Add the garlic and cook for another ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Set aside.

In a small #pot{}, heat the entire @Black Beans{1%can} (including the liquid!) with the cilantro stems and the remaining cumin over medium heat. Cook for about ~{4-5%minutes}, until heated through, then mash with a fork until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, wrap the @Flour Tortilla{4%unit} in #aluminium foil{}, then warm in the oven for ~{5%minutes}. Or, wrap them in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}.

Fill each tortilla with onions, peppers, mushrooms and black beans. Top with a dollop of @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, a spoonful of guacamole, and a sprinkle of the remaining cilantro. Olé!

> These fajitas are piled high with toppings: homemade refried beans, guacamole, and plenty of sautéed veggies. Poblano brings a nice, mild heat to the plate - be sure to cool it off with some tangy sour cream. Who knows, maybe Fajita Fridays will become the new Taco Tuesdays!